item.title: How do i fix this compiler error?
item.dc:creator: @zhshero-LTD zhshero-LTD
item.description:
@zhshero-LTD wrote:

Mr.czar:

Just because it’s 100 errors doesn’t always mean it’s a bracket and no need to repeat what was already said above…

if you noticed that what i said wasn’t not even said above me

100 errors are usually caused by a missing bracket. The reason you get 100 errors is because the maximum errors the compiler displays is 100. And the reason it gives you 100 errors, and it doesn't just say "missing bracket" is because the compiler doesn't know where the bracket should go.

Here is an example of how a missing bracket causes those errors:

[code]
public void exampleMethod() {
//do stuff in here
int x = 1;
//bracket should be here

public void anotherMethod() {
//do more stuff
}[/code]

That would give errors because the compiler would attempt to read it but there can’t be a method inside another method, which would ultimately cause a chain reaction into every method/field in the class.

Other tips: It won’t always be 100 errors, if the class is small or the missing bracket is near the end, it will be fewer errors.

The best way to fix 100 errors is to scroll to the top of the compiler and find which line the first error is on. Then you can look around that area to find the missing bracket.
